TERRAFORM FILE STRUCTURE AND ORGANIZATION

Create different files for different use case like variable.tf for variables storage, network.tf for n/w rsrc, dns.tf for dns, outputs.tf, firewall.tf,etc

Terraform processes all files together

Common Terraform files :

1. main.tf : commonly used for primary infrastructure components.
2.variables.tf : variables definitions used throughout your infra.
3.output.tf : output blocks to output values to the terminal or to use for inputs to other modules.
4.provider.tf : provider configurations and requirements
5.terraform.tfvars : Define the values for your variables-usually ignored by .gitignore.

ADDITIONAL FILES : 
6.terraform.tfstate : the file that terraform uses to store state.
7.terraform.tfstate.backup : backup of the previous state file before terraform writes anything new to the state file.
8. .terraform.lock.hcl : used to track and select provider versions
9. .gitignore : instructs git to ignore files included in this file.

WORKING DIRECTORY : 
terraform- > prod
                main.tf
                variables.tf
                output.tf
             test
